about.summary: Milksnake is an extension for setuptools that allows you to distribute dynamic linked libraries in Python wheels in the most portable way imaginable.

name: milksnake
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "milksnake" %}
{% set version = "0.1.5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.zip
  sha256: dfcd43b78bcf93897a75eea1dadf71c848319f19451cff4f3f3a628a5abe1688

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - cffi
  run:
    - cffi
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - milksnake
    - milksnake.ffi

about:
  home: http://github.com/simplejson/simplejson
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Milksnake is an extension for setuptools that allows you to distribute dynamic linked
            libraries in Python wheels in the most portable way imaginable.'
  doc_url: https://github.com/getsentry/milksnake/blob/master/README.md
  dev_url: https://github.com/getsentry/milksnake

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pacman82
    - xhochy
